ase cluster process includes series of decision points and readiness deposits  ...    interconnection and network upgrade costs.Phase 1 is similar to Part 1 of Class Year Study– and identifies cost estimates for CTOAFs (Connecting Transmission Owners’ Attachment Facilities), local SUFs (Supplemental Utility Facilities) and Distribution Upgrades.Phase 2 is similar to Part 2 of Class Year Study– and identifies cost estimates of SUFs and SDUs (System Deliverability Upgrades). Projects must pay a $4,000/MW readiness deposit (RD1) prior to entering Phase 1. Projects that choose to withdraw during this time must pay a withdrawal penalty of 50% of their study deposit and 10% of their RD1.  To enter Phase 2, projects must pay a second readiness deposit (RD2) of 20% of the upgrade costs estimated in Phase 1 or $4,000/MW, whichever is greater. Projects that choose to withdraw during this time must pay a withdrawal penalty of 100% of their study deposit and 20% of their RD2. At the conclusion of Phase 2, projects must pay a security deposit equal to the estimated cost of their SUFs, SDUs, and  ...    The series of decision points and readiness deposits throughout the NYISO’s cluster study process aims to accelerate  ...    Before transitioning to the new cluster study process, NYISO withdrew existing projects  in the queue  (except for certain advanced stage projects including those participating in the Class Year 2023 Study). As shown below, a total of 112 GW generation projects were withdrawn from the queue over May -July 2024. To participate in the Transition Cluster Study, projects, including those that are interested in re-joining the queue, must submit a new interconnection application and meet the study deposit and site control"
