        "# NYISO’s Order 2023 Transition Cluster Study\n* Report this article Divya BodduDivya Boddu\n### Divya Boddu\n#### Senior Energy Markets Consultant at ICF Published Sep 18, 2024\n+ Follow The application window for NYISO’s Transition Cluster Study recently opened on August 1, and projects planning to participate must meet the requisite application requirements by mid-October. This article describes NYISO’s Order 2023 Transition Cluster Study process, including milestone requirements and withdrawal of existing queue projects prior to the transition. It also outlines key considerations for project developers aiming to participate in the Transition  ...    NYISO submitted its compliance filing for FERC Order No. 2023 on May 1, 2024 and requested an effective date of May 2, 2024 for its proposed tariff changes. Order 2023 requires transmission providers to transition from serial  ...    Subsequently, NYISO’s Transition Cluster Application Window has opened recently on August 1, 2024 for a period of 75 business days. The overall timeline for the Transition Cluster Study is expected to take about 2 years to complete. Application Requirements include study deposit and full site control Projects intending to participate in the Transition Cluster Study, must submit the following prior to the close of the application window i.e. by October 15, 2024: * Application fees of $10,000 (or $5,000 for CRIS-only resources), and study deposits between $100,000 to $250,000, depending on the size of the project (or $50,000 for CRIS-only resources). * Demonstration of full site control of the facility, including technology specific acreage requirements * Details of POI, project layout etc. It can be noted that NYISO does not require the $5 million transition fee described in Order 2023.  ...    * Projects may withdraw without penalty within 5 days following the published list of cluster projects, after which the penalty will be equal to 25% their study deposit.  ...    The two-phase cluster process includes series of decision points and readiness deposits  ...    interconnection and network upgrade costs.Phase 1 is similar to Part 1 of Class Year Study– and identifies cost estimates for CTOAFs (Connecting Transmission Owners’ Attachment Facilities), local SUFs (Supplemental Utility Facilities) and Distribution Upgrades.Phase 2 is similar to Part 2 of Class Year Study– and identifies cost estimates of SUFs and SDUs (System Deliverability Upgrades). Projects must pay a $4,000/MW readiness deposit (RD1) prior to entering Phase 1. Projects that choose to withdraw during this time must pay a withdrawal penalty of 50% of their study deposit and 10% of their RD1.  To enter Phase 2, projects must pay a second readiness deposit (RD2) of 20% of the upgrade costs estimated in Phase 1 or $4,000/MW, whichever is greater. Projects that choose to withdraw during this time must pay a withdrawal penalty of 100% of their study deposit and 20% of their RD2. At the conclusion of Phase 2, projects must pay a security deposit equal to the estimated cost of their SUFs, SDUs, and  ...    The series of decision points and readiness deposits throughout the NYISO’s cluster study process aims to accelerate  ...    Before transitioning to the new cluster study process, NYISO withdrew existing projects  in the queue  (except for certain advanced stage projects including those participating in the Class Year 2023 Study). As shown below, a total of 112 GW generation projects were withdrawn from the queue over May -July 2024. To participate in the Transition Cluster Study, projects, including those that are interested in re-joining the queue, must submit a new interconnection application and meet the study deposit and site control"
